name: Josephine Lane
profile_summary: Our user is a 29-year-old woman who is a professional Registered Nurse in the Healthcare industry and has an ENFP personality type. She's originally from Phoenix, Arizona, but currently dating in Los Angeles, California. Having obtained a graduate degree from the University of Southern California, she is fluent in both English and Spanish. She identifies as a straight Hispanic/Latino, practicing Catholic with Scorpio as her zodiac sign. She values family, charity, and health & fitness strongly. Interesting activities she enjoys include yoga, cooking, reading, and travelling. Although currently without kids, she definitely wants children. She has a dog as her pet and leads an active lifestyle. Occasionally enjoys a drink but strictly says no to smoking, marijuana, and other drugs. She is specifically interested in a committed, long-term monogamous relationship.
preferences_summary: The user is looking for a man aged between 28 to 35 years, standing anywhere between 5'7" and 6'2" in height. Her potential partner should not have any children but should desire to have them in the future. She prefers a straight man who drinks occasionally but does not smoke or use marijuana or drugs. As far as physical preferences go, the man should lead an active lifestyle. The user is open to dating men from multiple ethnic backgrounds, including Black African Descent, East Asian, Hispanic/Latino, Middle Eastern, Native American, Pacific Islander, South Asian, Southeast Asian, and White Caucasian. She is okay with her partner having any political inclination (liberal, moderate, or conservative) and should be employed in sectors like healthcare, education, engineering, business, or law enforcement & security. The prospective partner should be able to communicate in English and resonate with values like family, charity, and health & fitness. She would like for him to also enjoy fitness, traveling, cooking, and should have either an undergraduate or graduate-level education.
